<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Arctostaphylos morroensis </i>is an erect, evergreen, sclerophyllous shrub. Leaves are closely overlapping, and they have upper shiny-green, convex surfaces and lower gray-tomentose surfaces. Their shape is truncate at the base. Plants lack a lignotuber, and seeds collect in a seed bank as stones. <i>A. morroensis </i>and <i>Eriodictyon altissimum </i>are CNPS list 1B.1 plants; <i>C. cuneatus </i>var. <i>fascicularis </i>is a CNPS list 4.2 plant. </div>
</div>

    
	
	
