    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Central California Coast</b> (261Ak). Stands occur in Montaña de Oro State Park (Odion and Tyler 2002).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Stands require periodic fire to maintain current species composition. Infrequent fire results in trees replacing the shrubs and decreasing seed bank quality. Frequent fire tends to convert the stands to coastal scrub or grassland. Thus, stands need a long fire cycle, approaching 100 years to accumulate a large seed bank (Odion and Tyler 2002). </div>
</div>

    

    

